    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last updated: March 10, 2026</p>

    <p>Vision Safe ("we", "our", or "us") operates the Vision Safe mobile application (the "App"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your information when you use our App.</p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

    <h3>a) Account Information</h3>
    <p>When you create an account, we collect:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Username and full name</li>
        <li>Email address</li>
        <li>Phone number</li>
        <li>Password (stored in encrypted form)</li>
        <li>Company name and job title (optional)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>b) Device and Camera Data</h3>
    <p>The App manages surveillance camera devices. We collect:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Camera device information (name, type, serial number, IP address)</li>
        <li>Device online/offline status</li>
        <li>Camera snapshots and video stream metadata</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>c) Environmental Sensor Data</h3>
    <p>The App may display environmental data from connected sensors, including temperature, humidity, CO2 levels, CO levels, VOC, particulate matter, and other air quality metrics.</p>

    <h3>d) Alert and Notification Data</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Alert records (type, severity, timestamp, associated device)</li>
        <li>Alert snapshot images</li>
        <li>Notification preferences and settings</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>e) Technical Data</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) device token for push notifications</li>
        <li>App version and device information</li>
        <li>Language preference</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use the collected information to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Provide and maintain the App's camera monitoring and alert services</li>
        <li>Authenticate your identity and manage your account</li>
        <li>Send push notifications for critical alerts and system events</li>
        <li>Display real-time environmental and device status data</li>
        <li>Improve the App's functionality and user experience</li>
        <li>Respond to your support requests</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Data Storage and Security</h2>
    <p>Your data is stored on secure servers. We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. Authentication tokens are stored locally on your device and transmitted securely.</p>

    <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>The App uses the following third-party services:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Firebase Cloud Messaging (Google)</strong> - for delivering push notifications. Subject to <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Firebase In-App Messaging (Google)</strong> - for in-app communication.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>These third-party services may collect information used to identify you. We encourage you to review their privacy policies.</p>

    <h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share your data only in the following circumstances:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>With your consent</li>
        <li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
        <li>To protect the rights and safety of our users and the public</li>
        <li>With service providers who assist us in operating the App (under strict confidentiality agreements)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain your personal data for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide the services. Alert data and sensor readings are retained according to system configuration. You may request deletion of your account and associated data at any time.</p>

    <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Access your personal data</li>
        <li>Update or correct your information</li>
        <li>Delete your account and all associated data</li>
        <li>Opt out of non-essential notifications</li>
        <li>Request a copy of your data</li>
    </ul>
    <p>You can exercise these rights through the App's Settings page or by contacting us directly.</p>

    <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>The App is not intended for use by children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal data, please contact us so we can take appropriate action.</p>

    <h2>9. Permissions</h2>
    <p>The App may request the following device permissions:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Internet</strong> - to communicate with our servers</li>
        <li><strong>Notifications</strong> - to send alert and system notifications</li>
        <li><strong>Storage</strong> - to save downloaded snapshots and files</li>
        <li><strong>Photo Library</strong> - to save images to your device gallery</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated revision date. We encourage you to review this page periodically for any changes.</p>

    <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
    <div class="contact-box">
        <p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:</p>
        <p><strong>Email:</strong> support@visionsafe.com</p>
        <p><strong>Application:</strong> Vision Safe</p>
    </div>

